{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847027667,"sessionID":"ses_28744ed6effecYWaPBNhQAOkVR","part":{"id":"prt_d78bb2fb0001SU8BVO2XIItbCC","messageID":"msg_d78bb24900017sCra8sJRfYNW3","sessionID":"ses_28744ed6effecYWaPBNhQAOkVR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1407a021e65b4092b79f489c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) timer-based cleanup mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-008\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: S\n13: - **Base Spec**: client-go library for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: The workloadmanager module manages Sandboxes (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter instances). Currently, expiration logic exists in `expiration.go` to determine if a Sandbox is expired based on:\n20: - TTL (Time To Live): 8 hours default\n21: - Idle timeout: 15 minutes default  \n22: - Max lifetime: 24 hours default\n23: - Stale state: Unknown/Failed state for more than 1 hour\n24: \n25: The cleanup logic in `cleanup.go` handles removal of orphaned Kubernetes resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs).\n26: \n27: However, there is no scheduled background process to automatically detect and clean up expired sandboxes. This delta adds a scheduled GC mechanism.\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Requirement: GC Worker Lifecycle\n32: \n33: ### Scenario: GC worker starts on server initialization\n34: \n35: **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with default GC configuration (GCEnabled=true, GCInterval=5m)\n36: **WHEN** the workloadmanager service starts\n37: **THEN** a background goroutine should start running with a ticker that fires every 5 minutes\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Scenario: GC worker can be disabled via configuration\n42: \n43: **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with GCEnabled set to false\n44: **WHEN** the workloadmanager service starts\n45: **THEN** no background GC goroutine should be started\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ### Scenario: GC interval is configurable\n50: \n51: **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with GCInterval set to 10 minutes\n52: **WHEN** the background GC goroutine runs\n53: **THEN** the ticker should fire every 10 minutes\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Scenario: GC worker stops gracefully on shutdown\n58: \n59: **GIVEN** a running GC background goroutine\n60: **WHEN** the WorkloadManager's Close() method is called\n61: **THEN** the GC goroutine should stop and not process any more sandboxes\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## Requirement: Expired Sandbox Detection\n66: \n67: ### Scenario: Detect TTL-expired sandbox\n68: \n69: **GIVEN** a Sandbox with CreatedAt time more than 8 hours ago and no ExpiresAt set\n70: **WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByTTL)\n71: **THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ### Scenario: Detect idle-timeout expired sandbox\n76: \n77: **GIVEN** a Sandbox with LastActivityAt more than 15 minutes ago\n78: **WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByIdleTimeout)\n79: **THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### Scenario: Detect max-lifetime expired sandbox\n84: \n85: **GIVEN** a Sandbox with CreatedAt more than 24 hours ago\n86: **WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByMaxLifetime)\n87: **THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### Scenario: Detect stale-state sandbox\n92: \n93: **GIVEN** a Sandbox in state \"Unknown\" or \"Failed\" with CreatedAt more than 1 hour ago\n94: **WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByStaleState)\n95: **THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## Requirement: Expired Sandbox Cleanup\n100: \n101: ### Scenario: Delete expired sandbox with default grace period\n102: \n103: **GIVEN** an expired Sandbox\n104: **WHEN** the GC worker triggers deletion\n105: **THEN** the Sandbox should be deleted with a 30-second grace period (default from expiration.go:CalculateGracePeriod)\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Scenario: Force delete stale sandbox\n110: \n111: **GIVEN** a Sandbox in stale state (Unknown/Failed) for more than 1 hour\n112: **WHEN** the GC worker triggers deletion\n113: **THEN** the Sandbox should be force-deleted with GracePeriodSeconds=0\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ### Scenario: Clean up orphaned Kubernetes resources\n118: \n119: **GIVEN** an expired Sandbox that created K8s resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs)\n120: **WHEN** the cleanup process runs (using cleanup.go:CleanupAllResources)\n121: **THEN** all owned Services, ConfigMaps, and PVCs should be deleted\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Scenario: Skip deletion of retained PVCs\n126: \n127: **GIVEN** an expired Sandbox with an owned PVC backed by a PersistentVolume with ReclaimPolicy=Retain\n128: **WHEN** the cleanup process attempts to delete the PVC\n129: **THEN** the PVC should be skipped and retained\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## Requirement: GC Metrics and Logging\n134: \n135: ### Scenario: Log GC cycle results\n136: \n137: **GIVEN** the GC worker running\n138: **WHEN** a GC cycle completes\n139: **THEN** it should log the number of sandboxes scanned and the number cleaned\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ### Scenario: Log cleanup details per sandbox\n144: \n145: **GIVEN** an expired Sandbox being cleaned up\n146: **WHEN** cleanup completes\n147: **THEN** it should log which resources were cleaned (Service/ConfigMap/PVC names)\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ## Configuration\n152: \n153: The following configuration options should be available:\n154: \n155: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n156: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n157: | GCEnabled | bool | true | Enable/disable GC background worker |\n158: | GCInterval | time.Duration | 5m | Interval between GC cycles |\n159: | GCBatchSize | int | 50 | Max sandboxes to process per cycle |\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Dependencies\n164: \n165: - `expiration.go` - Existing expiration detection logic (isExpired, isExpiredByTTL, isExpiredByIdleTimeout, etc.)\n166: - `cleanup.go` - Existing resource cleanup logic (CleanupManager)\n167: - Uses client-go for K8s operations\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Implementation Notes\n172: \n173: New file to create: `pkg/workloadmanager/gc.go`\n174: \n175: The GC worker should:\n176: 1. Accept a context and stop channel for graceful shutdown\n177: 2. Use a time.Ticker for periodic execution\n178: 3. Call ListSandboxes to get all sandboxes\n179: 4. Filter expired ones using existing isExpired() function\n180: 5. Delete expired sandboxes via WorkloadManager\n181: 6. Clean up orphaned resources using CleanupManager\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Acceptance Criteria\n186: \n187: - [ ] GC background worker starts automatically when workloadmanager starts (if GCEnabled=true)\n188: - [ ] GC can be disabled via configuration (GCEnabled=false)\n189: - [ ] GC interval is configurable (default 5 minutes)\n190: - [ ] GC worker stops gracefully on WorkloadManager Close()\n191: - [ ] All four expiration types (TTL, idle, max lifetime, stale) are correctly detected\n192: - [ ] Expired sandboxes are deleted with appropriate grace period\n193: - [ ] Force deletion (GracePeriodSeconds=0) is used for stale sandboxes\n194: - [ ] Orphaned K8s resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs) are cleaned up\n195: - [ ] PVCs with Retain policy are skipped during cleanup\n196: - [ ] GC cycle results are logged (scanned count, cleaned count)\n197: - [ ] Cleanup details are logged per sandbox\n\n(End of file - total 197 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) timer-based cleanup mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-008\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Base Spec**: client-go library for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe workloadmanager module manages Sandboxes (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter instances). Currently, expiration logic exists in `expiration.go` to determine if a Sandbox is expired based on:\n- TTL (Time To Live): 8 hours default","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775847027631,"end":1775847027663}}}}
