{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847058495,"sessionID":"ses_28744ed6effecYWaPBNhQAOkVR","part":{"id":"prt_d78bb9689001JGXautYfR53hl1","messageID":"msg_d78bb8dd40016TqffkW9nbhw2S","sessionID":"ses_28744ed6effecYWaPBNhQAOkVR","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_7f184e1c88404164adfc28c5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the HTTP reverse proxy core in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-009\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module is responsible for routing HTTP requests to backend Sandbox services. This delta implements the core HTTP reverse proxy functionality.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Proxy Core\n\n### Scenario: Proxy HTTP requests to backend\n\n**GIVEN** an HTTP request to the router\n**WHEN** the request matches a configured route\n**THEN** the request SHOULD be proxied to the appropriate backend service\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] HTTP proxy core functionality implemented\n- [ ] Route matching works correctly\n- [ ] Requests are forwarded to backend services","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775847058485,"end":1775847058493}}}}
